item.description:
fixed: <p>
You can tweak the admin menu font for localized package in the same way azaozz suggested in <a class="closed ticket" href="http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/8472" title="#8472: defect (bug): Too small fields for transtations (closed: fixed)">#8472</a>.
</p>
<p>
Here is the example function to put into <code>wp-content/languages/pt_BR.php</code> which I used in my test:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">function br_change_admin_menu_font() { ?&gt;
&lt;style type="text/css"&gt;
	#adminmenu {
		font-family: Arial, "Bitstream Vera Sans", Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif;
	}
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;?php
}
add_action('admin_head', 'br_change_admin_menu_font');
</pre><p>
Since this ticket was closed on a completed milestone, a new ticket should be opened for any further issues. Re-closing as fixed for 3.2.1.
</p>
